<TITLE> Ha-Mim Group sues 1600 for arson </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 6 (bdnews24.com)The management of a Ha-Mim Group sweater factory has filed a case against some 1600 unnamed workers for arson and vandalism following three days of riots at Ashulia that left two dead and the factory on fire. Md Nazrul Islam, executive director of the sweater factory, filed the case in Ashulia at dead of night, police said on Monday. Ashulia police sub inspector Golam Masud, also investigation officer in the case, said they would also hold raids at night "to catch the suspects". Two workers were killed when law enforcing agencies opened fire into crowds of demonstrators during the unrest at an industrial zone on the outskirts of the capital from Jun 28-30. Agitating workers later set fire to the Ha-Mim Group factory. Ashulia police chief Monwar Hossain told bdnews24.com the case statement alleged some 1500 to 1600 unnamed protestors from outside entered the factory breaking open its main gate. "They beat up security guards and set the factory and its store ablaze with petrol. They also torched a number of vehicles," said Hossain. Quoting the case documents, he said the factory claimed losses from the fire amounting to over Tk 48 crore. bdnews24.co
